<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38218h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38218h">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38218h"> 218(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Manu</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The determination to keep their race pure and dominant led the Hindu lawgivers, typified by <mark>Manu</mark> (the code called by his name may have been contemporary with that of Moses), to prevent for all time any kind of social intercourse between their people and people of other races, including outcastes &mdash; the aliens with whom they were in actual contact. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 22</small></blockquote> . <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: not copied</mm></dd> </dd></dl>
